data.content:
noun
plural -outs
[count] a person who refuses to reach an agreement until certain terms are met :a person who holds out
He says he might be a holdout at the start of the next season if the team doesn't agree to pay him more.
an act of holding out for something
He is expected to end his three-week holdout and join the team tomorrow.
a person who continues to do or use something after others have stopped doing or using it
A few holdouts still use typewriters, but nearly everybody uses computers now. - see also hold out at 1hold

Danh từ
(từ Mỹ,nghĩa Mỹ), (thông tục) đấu thủ nhà nghề (bóng đá, bóng chày...) không ký giao kèo khi đến hạn để đòi điều kiện cao hơn
